<subsection xml:id="subsec-construction-of-a-circle-touching-the-vertices-of-a-triangle">
        <title>Construction of a circle touching the vertices of a triangle</title>
        <p>
            A circle touching the vertices(corners) of a triangle is called <term>circumscribed circle.</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            For your activity, construct a circumscribed circle for the given triangle. Follow the instructions below. 
        </p>
        <p>
            <term>Instructions</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select the <term>perpendicular bisector tool(Window)</term> and click on the points <m>A \text { and } B</m>
                        to construct a perpendicular line cutting through segment <m>AB</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Click on the points <m>A \text { and } C</m> to construct another perpendicular line cutting through segment <m>AC.</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select <term>intersect tool(Window)</term> and mark the point of intersection <m>D,</m>of the two perpendicular lines. 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select <term>circle with center tool(Window)</term> and click at points <m>D</m> and  <m>A</m> to construct the circle. 
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>

        <figure>
            <caption>Circumscribed circle</caption>
            <interactive xml:id="geogebra-Circumscribed-circle" platform="geogebra" width="95%" aspect="4:3">
